observationText: The HPAF-II cell line was one of the cell lines used to compare different shRNA scoring approaches for identifying essential genes.
The HPAF-II cell line was included in a proteomic analysis comparing the phosphoproteomic profiles of multiple pancreatic cancer cell lines.
The HPAF-II cell line was derived from a pancreatic adenocarcinoma and is known to produce abundant mucin as well as carcinoembryonic antigen.
